rComments: Best prof so much! I really enjoyed our applied project. Inspirational talker and always available to answer our inquiries!
Good presenter. Really interesting  project requiring a lot of work in very little time.
Best teacher ive had so far.. very interesting, knows how to use his many experiences for class examples. I recommend him.

Great Prof. There is alot of case studies. He is the first teacher I have been able to go to all his 3hr lectures and pay attention the entire time. He has a unique way of teaching and if you listen instead of reading the book. You will succeed.

Loves to talk about himself. On a 3hr class, he spends easily 30 min talking about his "many successes in his short life". Easy assignements, somewhat easy exams (final is all multiple choices), and although you have to attend the class for his "pop case studies", it is honestly useless to attedn his class because he is VERY VERY repetitive.

One if not the best teachers i've had at Ottawa U. Very interesting, has a way to tie in his experiences with the subject matter. His grading is a little tough though. Most of his exams are multiple choice, so often you'll have to choose the answer which is MORE correct. argh...but study EXACTLY what he teaches instead of the book and you're good.

terrible prof. rarely teaches and mostly talks about his family. case studies make classes mandatory and he removes marks for using the text book answers. final was multiple choice and was not related to class or text book. expect a mediocre grade if you take this class.

Pretty good prof. Very charismatic and knows what he is talking about. Had him in 3 hour classes and rarely got bored (which is extremely rare). Only major drawback are his exams. Most are multiple choice only which can lead to crappy grades even after moderate study.
best professor ever! Totally understanding his field ! Very helpful, always available ! He helps us with his very interesting experience...Le meilleur prof !
